Madison Small, from Ashburn, Virginia, left school early on Monday morning .
On Friday afternoon, her father, Tim Small, contacted the Broad Run High School to tell staff that her daughter had passed away .
By Tuesday afternoon, the Loudoun County Health Department confirmed she died of meningococcal meningitis .
The bacteria causes membranes covering the brain and spinal cord to swell .
It is the school system's first confirmed case in two years .